      • oneTimeEvent

        public static void oneTimeEvent​(android.content.Context context,
                                int id,
                                OneTimeEventInterface eventInterface)
        Call this method to do something for one or more time. In OneTimeEventInterface method, you have to return true if you want event to occur for one more time. false otherwise. Event is the code that has to be executed.
        Parameters:
        eventInterface - The interface that include the event.
        id - The unique id for this event.

      • oneTimeDialog

        public static void oneTimeDialog​(android.content.Context context,
                                 int id,
                                 OneTimeDialogInterface dialogInterface)
        Call this method to show alertdialog for one or more time. In OneTimeDialogInterface method, you have to return true if you want to show alertdialog for one more time, false otherwise. You don't need to call AlertDialog.Builder.show() method.
        Parameters:
        dialogInterface - The interface that include alertdialog code.
        id - The unique id for this alertdialog.
